[
  {
    "startTime": 12.942,
    "endTime": 14.633000000000001,
    "text": "Last year ..."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 14.657,
    "endTime": 15.86,
    "text": "was hell."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 15.884,
    "endTime": 17.682000000000002,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 20.391,
    "endTime": 23.942,
    "text": "It was my first time eating Nigerian \"jollof.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 23.967,
    "endTime": 25.549,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 26.436,
    "endTime": 29.295,
    "text": "Actually, in all seriousness,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 29.319,
    "endTime": 32.132,
    "text": "I was going through a lot of personal turmoil."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.55,
    "endTime": 35.236,
    "text": "Faced with enormous stress,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 35.26,
    "endTime": 37.283,
    "text": "I suffered an anxiety attack."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 38.362,
    "endTime": 41.52,
    "text": "On some days, I could do no work."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.156,
    "endTime": 44.519999999999996,
    "text": "On other days,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 44.76,
    "endTime": 47.364999999999995,
    "text": "I just wanted to lay in my bed and cry."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 48.478,
    "endTime": 53.727000000000004,
    "text": "My doctor asked if I'd like to speak with a mental health professional"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 53.751,
    "endTime": 55.854,
    "text": "about my stress and anxiety."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 56.589,
    "endTime": 57.891,
    "text": "Mental health?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 58.792,
    "endTime": 62.682,
    "text": "I clammed up and violently shook my head in protest."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 65.65,
    "endTime": 68.81700000000001,
    "text": "I felt a profound sense of a shame."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 70.233,
    "endTime": 73.671,
    "text": "I felt the weight of stigma."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 74.959,
    "endTime": 77.318,
    "text": "I have a loving, supportive family"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 77.342,
    "endTime": 79.649,
    "text": "and incredibly loyal friends,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 79.673,
    "endTime": 84.242,
    "text": "yet I could not entertain the idea of speaking to anyone"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 84.266,
    "endTime": 86.296,
    "text": "about my feeling of pain."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 87.824,
    "endTime": 92.291,
    "text": "I felt suffocated by the rigid architecture"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 92.315,
    "endTime": 94.605,
    "text": "of our African masculinity."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 95.585,
    "endTime": 97.699,
    "text": "\"People have real problems, Sangu."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 97.724,
    "endTime": 99.179,
    "text": "Get over yourself!\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 100.776,
    "endTime": 102.756,
    "text": "The first time I heard \"mental health,\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 103.7,
    "endTime": 107.663,
    "text": "I was a boarding school student fresh off the boat from Ghana,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 107.687,
    "endTime": 109.618,
    "text": "at the Peddie School in New Jersey."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 110.887,
    "endTime": 114.293,
    "text": "I had just gone through the brutal experience"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 114.317,
    "endTime": 116.869,
    "text": "of losing seven loved ones in the same month."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 118.389,
    "endTime": 119.845,
    "text": "The school nurse,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 119.869,
    "endTime": 123.93299999999999,
    "text": "concerned about what I'd gone through -- God bless her soul --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 123.957,
    "endTime": 125.907,
    "text": "she inquired about my mental health."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 127.246,
    "endTime": 129.228,
    "text": "\"Is she mental?\" I thought."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 130.33,
    "endTime": 132.477,
    "text": "Does she not know I'm an African man?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 132.502,
    "endTime": 133.51600000000002,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 133.54,
    "endTime": 135.411,
    "text": "Like Okonkwo in \"Things Fall Apart,\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 135.435,
    "endTime": 140.176,
    "text": "we African men neither process nor express our emotions."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 140.791,
    "endTime": 142.482,
    "text": "We deal with our problems."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 142.506,
    "endTime": 144.49,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 145.1,
    "endTime": 147.0,
    "text": "We deal with our problems."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 147.24,
    "endTime": 151.79500000000002,
    "text": "I called my brother and laughed about \"Oyibo\" people -- white people --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 151.819,
    "endTime": 153.676,
    "text": "and their strange diseases --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 153.7,
    "endTime": 156.938,
    "text": "depression, ADD and those \"weird things.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 158.32,
    "endTime": 160.311,
    "text": "Growing up in West Africa,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 160.335,
    "endTime": 164.716,
    "text": "when people used the term \"mental,\" what came to mind was a madman"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 164.74,
    "endTime": 166.983,
    "text": "with dirty, dread-locked hair,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 167.7,
    "endTime": 169.783,
    "text": "bumbling around half-naked on the streets."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.904,
    "endTime": 172.724,
    "text": "We all know this man."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 172.748,
    "endTime": 175.29,
    "text": "Our parents warned us about him."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 175.64,
    "endTime": 177.184,
    "text": "\"Mommy, mommy, why is he mad?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 177.209,
    "endTime": 178.421,
    "text": "\"Drugs!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 178.445,
    "endTime": 180.834,
    "text": "If you even look at drugs, you end up like him.\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 180.858,
    "endTime": 182.47,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 182.8,
    "endTime": 184.865,
    "text": "Come down with pneumonia,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.889,
    "endTime": 187.42100000000002,
    "text": "and your mother will rush you to the nearest hospital"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 187.445,
    "endTime": 188.827,
    "text": "for medical treatment."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 189.91,
    "endTime": 192.526,
    "text": "But dare to declare depression,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 193.278,
    "endTime": 196.679,
    "text": "and your local pastor will be driving out demons"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 196.704,
    "endTime": 198.548,
    "text": "and blaming witches in your village."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 199.118,
    "endTime": 202.18,
    "text": "According to the World Health Organization,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 202.42,
    "endTime": 205.1,
    "text": "mental health is about being able to cope"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 205.124,
    "endTime": 206.823,
    "text": "with the normal stressors of life;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 207.741,
    "endTime": 211.18400000000003,
    "text": "to work productively and fruitfully;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.208,
    "endTime": 214.835,
    "text": "and to be able to make a contribution to your community."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 215.321,
    "endTime": 221.933,
    "text": "Mental health includes our emotional, psychological and social well-being."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 222.676,
    "endTime": 227.435,
    "text": "Globally, 75 percent of all mental illness cases"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 227.46,
    "endTime": 230.94,
    "text": "can be found in low-income countries."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.118,
    "endTime": 231.95,
    "text": "Yet most African governments"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 231.974,
    "endTime": 236.17999999999998,
    "text": "invest less than one percent of their health care budget"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 236.205,
    "endTime": 237.48100000000002,
    "text": "in mental health."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 238.501,
    "endTime": 239.681,
    "text": "Even worse,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 239.705,
    "endTime": 243.824,
    "text": "we have a severe shortage of psychiatrists in Africa."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 244.656,
    "endTime": 248.939,
    "text": "Nigeria, for example, is estimated to have 200 --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 249.632,
    "endTime": 252.653,
    "text": "in a country of almost 200 million."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 254.242,
    "endTime": 255.70999999999998,
    "text": "In all of Africa,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 255.735,
    "endTime": 259.63800000000003,
    "text": "90 percent of our people lack access to treatment."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 260.5,
    "endTime": 262.253,
    "text": "As a result,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 262.278,
    "endTime": 265.28200000000004,
    "text": "we suffer in solitude,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 265.306,
    "endTime": 267.75,
    "text": "silenced by stigma."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 269.318,
    "endTime": 273.993,
    "text": "We as Africans often respond to mental health with distance,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 274.664,
    "endTime": 275.866,
    "text": "ignorance,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 276.355,
    "endTime": 277.533,
    "text": "guilt,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 277.954,
    "endTime": 279.16,
    "text": "fear"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 279.754,
    "endTime": 281.40000000000003,
    "text": "and anger."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 282.129,
    "endTime": 286.80600000000004,
    "text": "In a study conducted by Arboleda-Fl√≥rez,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 286.83,
    "endTime": 290.488,
    "text": "directly asking, \"What is the cause of mental illness?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 291.487,
    "endTime": 296.771,
    "text": "34 percent of Nigerian respondents cited drug misuse;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 298.16,
    "endTime": 303.34400000000005,
    "text": "19 percent said divine wrath and the will of God --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 303.368,
    "endTime": 304.673,
    "text": "(Laughter)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 305.27,
    "endTime": 306.728,
    "text": "12 percent,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 307.95,
    "endTime": 310.716,
    "text": "witchcraft and spiritual possession."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 311.616,
    "endTime": 316.176,
    "text": "But few cited other known causes of mental illness,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 316.2,
    "endTime": 317.846,
    "text": "like genetics,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 317.87,
    "endTime": 319.806,
    "text": "socioeconomic status,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 319.83,
    "endTime": 321.425,
    "text": "war,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 321.449,
    "endTime": 322.862,
    "text": "conflict"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 322.886,
    "endTime": 324.401,
    "text": "or the loss of a loved one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 325.829,
    "endTime": 328.716,
    "text": "The stigmatization against mental illness"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 328.74,
    "endTime": 333.206,
    "text": "often results in the ostracizing and demonizing of sufferers."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.255,
    "endTime": 338.251,
    "text": "Photojournalist Robin Hammond has documented some of these abuses ..."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 338.275,
    "endTime": 339.667,
    "text": "in Uganda,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 340.665,
    "endTime": 341.994,
    "text": "in Somalia,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 343.89,
    "endTime": 344.918,
    "text": "and here in Nigeria."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 347.374,
    "endTime": 348.716,
    "text": "For me,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 349.877,
    "endTime": 352.196,
    "text": "the stigma is personal."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 353.942,
    "endTime": 355.571,
    "text": "In 2009,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 356.616,
    "endTime": 359.722,
    "text": "I received a frantic call in the middle of the night."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 361.179,
    "endTime": 363.527,
    "text": "My best friend in the world --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 363.551,
    "endTime": 368.69,
    "text": "a brilliant, philosophical, charming, hip young man --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 368.714,
    "endTime": 370.865,
    "text": "was diagnosed with schizophrenia."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 372.424,
    "endTime": 376.842,
    "text": "I witnessed some of the friends we'd grown up with recoil."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 379.136,
    "endTime": 380.65900000000005,
    "text": "I heard the snickers."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 381.448,
    "endTime": 383.39,
    "text": "I heard the whispers."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 384.6,
    "endTime": 386.23600000000005,
    "text": "\"Did you hear he has gone mad?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 387.95,
    "endTime": 389.625,
    "text": "(Kru English) \"He has gone crazy!\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 389.669,
    "endTime": 393.989,
    "text": "Derogatory, demeaning commentary about his condition --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 394.13,
    "endTime": 397.989,
    "text": "words we would never say about someone with cancer"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 398.14,
    "endTime": 399.774,
    "text": "or someone with malaria."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 400.484,
    "endTime": 404.162,
    "text": "Somehow, when it comes to mental illness,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 404.187,
    "endTime": 407.237,
    "text": "our ignorance eviscerates all empathy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 408.539,
    "endTime": 412.707,
    "text": "I stood by his side as his community isolated him,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 413.98,
    "endTime": 416.312,
    "text": "but our love never wavered."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 417.668,
    "endTime": 420.747,
    "text": "Tacitly, I became passionate about mental health."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 421.694,
    "endTime": 424.326,
    "text": "Inspired by his plight,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 424.35,
    "endTime": 427.673,
    "text": "I helped found the mental health special interest alumni group"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 427.697,
    "endTime": 429.352,
    "text": "at my college."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 429.376,
    "endTime": 432.753,
    "text": "And during my tenure as a resident tutor in graduate school,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 432.777,
    "endTime": 436.739,
    "text": "I supported many undergraduates with their mental health challenges."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 437.271,
    "endTime": 439.786,
    "text": "I saw African students struggle"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 439.81,
    "endTime": 441.647,
    "text": "and unable to speak to anyone."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 442.566,
    "endTime": 446.561,
    "text": "Even with this knowledge and with their stories in tow,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 446.586,
    "endTime": 448.572,
    "text": "I, in turn, struggled,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 448.596,
    "endTime": 453.169,
    "text": "and could not speak to anyone when I faced my own anxiety,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 453.193,
    "endTime": 457.155,
    "text": "so deep is our fear of being the madman."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 459.735,
    "endTime": 460.933,
    "text": "All of us --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 461.698,
    "endTime": 463.885,
    "text": "but we Africans especially --"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 464.775,
    "endTime": 470.681,
    "text": "need to realize that our mental struggles do not detract from our virility,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 470.706,
    "endTime": 473.59700000000004,
    "text": "nor does our trauma taint our strength."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 474.756,
    "endTime": 479.465,
    "text": "We need to see mental health as important as physical health."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 480.403,
    "endTime": 484.80600000000004,
    "text": "We need to stop suffering in silence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 485.939,
    "endTime": 489.39700000000005,
    "text": "We must stop stigmatizing disease"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 489.421,
    "endTime": 491.627,
    "text": "and traumatizing the afflicted."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 493.399,
    "endTime": 494.858,
    "text": "Talk to your friends."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 495.834,
    "endTime": 497.41,
    "text": "Talk to your loved ones."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 498.394,
    "endTime": 500.159,
    "text": "Talk to health professionals."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 501.437,
    "endTime": 502.71500000000003,
    "text": "Be vulnerable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 503.615,
    "endTime": 505.492,
    "text": "Do so with the confidence"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 506.335,
    "endTime": 508.861,
    "text": "that you are not alone."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 510.11,
    "endTime": 512.191,
    "text": "Speak up if you're struggling."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 514.414,
    "endTime": 517.941,
    "text": "Being honest about how we feel"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 517.965,
    "endTime": 519.624,
    "text": "does not make us weak;"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 520.629,
    "endTime": 522.172,
    "text": "it makes us human."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 523.499,
    "endTime": 528.45,
    "text": "It is time to end the stigma associated with mental illness."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 528.93,
    "endTime": 532.3399999999999,
    "text": "So the next time your hear \"mental,\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 533.228,
    "endTime": 535.223,
    "text": "do not just think of the madman."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 536.163,
    "endTime": 537.372,
    "text": "Think of me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 537.796,
    "endTime": 539.72,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 539.744,
    "endTime": 541.27,
    "text": "Thank you."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 541.51,
    "endTime": 545.43,
    "text": "(Applause)"
  }
]